*asterisk-10.3.1 (24 Apr 2012)
*asterisk-1.8.11.1 (24 Apr 2012)

  24 Apr 2012; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +asterisk-1.8.11.1.ebuild,
  +asterisk-10.3.1.ebuild:
  Updates on the 1.8 & 10 branches addressing a permission escalation in the
  manager interface (AST-2012-004/CVE-2012-2414), a heap buffer overflow in the
  SCCP channel driver (AST-2012-005/CVE-2012-2415) and a remote crash
  vulnerability in the SIP channel driver (AST-2012-006/CVE-2012-2416).

  10 Apr 2012; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> -asterisk-1.8.8.2.ebuild:
  Remove vulnerable ebuild for security bug #408431 by Tim Sammut.

*asterisk-1.8.11.0 (10 Apr 2012)

  10 Apr 2012; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +asterisk-1.8.11.0.ebuild:
  Upstream bugfix release, addressing a potential buffer overrun & memory leak
  for sip show peers, ACK routing for non-2xx responses, insufficient locking
  in res_odbc, blind transfer parking issues, loss of CDR variables when
  bridging and a desync between analog signalling & DAHDI with regard to the
  outgoing flag. Trunk frequency fixes now partially applied upstream, still
  carrying one patch by Jaco Kroon. Downstream patchset down to 13 patches now.

*asterisk-10.3.0 (30 Mar 2012)

  30 Mar 2012; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +asterisk-10.3.0.ebuild:
  New upstream bugfix release, addressing a potential buffer overrun & memory
  leak for sip show peers, ACK routing for non-2xx responses, insufficient
  locking in res_odbc, blind transfer parking issues, loss of CDR variables
  when bridging and a desync between analog signalling & DAHDI with regard to
  the outgoing flag. Trunk frequency fixes now partially applied upstream,
  still carrying one patch by Jaco Kroon. Downstream patchset down to 12
  patches now.

